                            <comment id="320077" author="adilger" created="Sat, 4 Dec 2021 22:43:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This subtest is also failing intermittently with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;multiop still running&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, since 2020-06-22 (several times) when the test was first added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/39139&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/39139&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13693&quot; title=&quot;lfs getstripe should avoid opening regular files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13693&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lfs: avoid opening regular files for getstripe&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, so I suspect the test is just not very robust. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For 2021-11 there were 5 failures in 2764 runs, so the actual failure rate is very low v&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
